            "answer_text": "Look at the years on the timeline: 10 BC, 9 BC, 8 BC, 7 BC, 6 BC, 5 BC, 4 BC, 3 BC, 2 BC, 1 BC, 1 AD, 2 AD, 3 AD, 4 AD, 5 AD, 6 AD, 7 AD, 8 AD, 9 AD, 10 AD\u2026\u2026\u20262015, 2016, 2017, 2018, 2019 You didn\u2019t see 0 AD, did you? That\u2019s because 0 didn\u2019t exist at the time. 0 was invented somewhere around 600 AD. 1 AD does not mean a year after the \u201cyear of the lord\u201d. It means the it\u2019s the 1st year. When you are 0 years old, it\u2019s your 1st year of life. Not your 0th. You turn 1 when your 1st year ends and your 2nd year begins. I\u2019m 22 but it\u2019s actually my 23rd year. ",
