            "answer_text": "None. We assume that the current calendar was in effect back in those times. The Gregorian calendar didn\u2019t come along for over a thousand years since \u201cyear 1\u201d. They didn\u2019t measure years like, 1 BC 0 1 AD back then. The Gregorian calendar restarted the yearly markoff by calling this year 1 (presumably by the birth of Jesus. Remember it was the Christian church and Pope Gregory which started the Gregorian calendar). So how many years passed between 1 BC and 1 AD? None. It just got renumbered. ",
